CSRC Says Pushing to Streamline Corporate Bond Sale Approvals

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-03-07T08:34:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/csrc-says-pushing-to-streamline-corporate-bond-sale-approvals.html
The China Securities Regulatory
Commission is pushing to streamline the approval process for
corporate bond sales and to also make follow-on stock offerings
easier, Assistant Chairman Zhu Congjiu said at a briefing in
Beijing today.  Follow-on stock offerings may be made easier soon, Zhu said
today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
